neofontrender.tooltip.enabled=Enable or disable Neo Font Render.
neofontrender.tooltip.engine=Switch between SFR, Skia, and vanilla Minecraft text rendering.
neofontrender.tooltip.string_mode=Skia only: render a whole formatted string at once for shaping, ligatures, kerning, emoji ZWJ, and BiDi.
neofontrender.tooltip.autobase=Automatically align the selected font baseline to Minecraft UI text.
neofontrender.tooltip.antialias=Choose the AWT text antialiasing mode used by the SFR glyph rasterizer.
neofontrender.tooltip.fractional=Use fractional font metrics for more precise glyph positions.
neofontrender.tooltip.style=Cycle the forced font style: plain, bold, italic, or bold italic.
neofontrender.tooltip.builtins=Always append bundled fallback fonts such as Noto Color Emoji.
neofontrender.tooltip.autoscale=Cap effective raster scale to the current GUI pixel scale. Turn off to use the manual oversample value directly.
neofontrender.tooltip.linear=Use linear texture filtering when the current raster scale needs interpolation.
neofontrender.tooltip.mipmap=Enable mipmaps for font textures. This can help distant/scaled text but may soften UI text.
neofontrender.tooltip.pipeline=Dedicated blend/shader pipeline. Keep this OFF for color emoji; enabling it can change emoji colors.
neofontrender.tooltip.shader=Use a small shader to boost thin antialiased edges. Disable this if colorful emoji look too bright.
neofontrender.tooltip.edge_bleed=Fill transparent Skia texture pixels from nearby colors to avoid dark fringes around text and emoji.
neofontrender.tooltip.gpu_offscreen=Skia only: rasterize text on an isolated hidden OpenGL context. Enabling this defaults to CPU texture submit to avoid the still-experimental shared texture path touching game render state.
neofontrender.tooltip.gpu_cpu_submit=Skia GPU only: read pixels back after GPU rasterization, then submit through Minecraft DynamicTexture. This is the current default stable path; disable it only to test experimental direct shared textures.
neofontrender.tooltip.monochrome_text=Skia only: rasterize single-color text as white glyphs and tint with vertex color at draw time, reusing one glyph texture across all colors instead of re-rasterizing per color. Greatly improves cache hit rate. Requires premultipliedAlpha to take effect.
neofontrender.tooltip.premultiplied_alpha=Skia: upload glyph textures with premultiplied alpha and composite with premultiplied blending. Required for monochrome tint and GPU offscreen to take effect. Changes how all text blends; turn off if colors look wrong.
neofontrender.tooltip.integer_scale=When auto scale is enabled, use nearest sampling for near-integer scale ratios to keep UI text sharp.
neofontrender.tooltip.cosmic_variant_font_only=When bold, italic, or bold-italic has an override, only switch to that font without additionally applying bold or italic styling. Empty overrides still use automatic style matching.
neofontrender.tooltip.high_mag=When auto scale is enabled, use nearest sampling for highly magnified text so linear filtering does not soften edges.
neofontrender.tooltip.anisotropic=When auto scale is enabled, use anisotropic filtering for perspective/world text to improve angled or distant text.
neofontrender.tooltip.debug_stats=Collect font cache hit/miss/eviction counters, segmentation counters, and raster pixel statistics. Enable for diagnostics; keep off for normal gameplay.
neofontrender.tooltip.sign_model_lod=Use flat distant sign geometry with the original texture. This reduces model vertices/display-list calls but not per-sign TESR dispatch, so its standalone gain can be limited.
neofontrender.tooltip.sign_cross_batch=Collect distant vanilla signs during Forge's TESR pass, submit models once, then draw text. Disable and restart to remove the dispatcher Mixin if incompatible.
neofontrender.tooltip.sign_occlusion=Cache and stagger multiple board sight-line tests; skip the complete sign renderer only when every sample is blocked by an opaque full cube.
